    "created_at": "2024-07-29T10:24:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-07-29T10:24:46Z",
    "body": "Potentially related issues: #5800, #5583\r\n\r\nI'm seeing a very similar issue, in my case apparently caused by a custom module:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[custom.kubernetes]\r\ncommand = \"kubectl config current-context\"\r\nwhen = \"env | grep -c KUBE\"\r\nstyle = \"cyan bold\"\r\nsymbol = \"☸ \"\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, in a terminal where the command given at `when` prints `0` (i.e. the module should be skipped):\r\n\r\n```\r\n🐧❯ time sh -c 'env | grep -c \"KUBE\"'\r\n0\r\n\r\n________________________________________________________\r\nExecuted in    4,03 millis    fish           external \r\n   usr time    3,49 millis  456,00 micros    3,03 millis \r\n   sys time    1,80 millis  108,00 micros    1,70 millis \r\n```\r\n\r\nThe plugin still takes a considerable amount of time:\r\n\r\n```\r\n🐧❯ starship timings\r\n\r\n Here are the timings of modules in your prompt (>=1ms or output):\r\n custom.kubernetes  -  389ms  -   \"\"\r\n battery            -    4ms  -   \"\"\r\n directory          -   <1ms  -   \"~ \"\r\n line_break         -   <1ms  -   \"\\n\"\r\n character          -   <1ms  -   \"🐧❯ \"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I comment out `custom.kubernetes`, the overhead vanishes:\r\n\r\n```\r\n🐧❯ starship timings\r\n\r\n Here are the timings of modules in your prompt (>=1ms or output):\r\n battery     -   4ms  -   \"\"\r\n directory   -  <1ms  -   \"~ \"\r\n line_break  -  <1ms  -   \"\\n\"\r\n character   -  <1ms  -   \"🐧❯ \"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThose ≈400ms delay on every prompt rendering are _very_ noticeable, and the value is even higher if the system is under load.\r\n",
